<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I don't use Cool'n'Quiet (CnQ). Heck, my system is pretty quiet but it's anything but cool as I'm throttling every bit of juice I can out of it at all times. I really don't see why you would need CnQ myself since the cpu automatically draws less power when at idle than when you're doing something like playing games. An Athlon64 3000 should be running at 1.8ghz tops unless CnQt overclocks it slightly. I'd try turning off the CnQ feature and see if that helps. Unless it's a portable system (laptops) or you are in a very hot environment (server rooms or non ventilated room in summer) then CnQ really does nothing for you.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
