<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Hm, played a bit with Windows` power safe settings and managed the CPU to switch faster.
<br />
The real problem isn't CnQ at all, the problem is the bad timer implementation of EQ depending on the cpus frequency <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />
As for the frequency, full speed are 2GHz, not 1800 MHz. Power safe is 1GHz, and it makes 10 degrees of temperature difference...</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
