<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Ok, did some research and your processor is an Athlon64 3000+. Same as mine except that mine is a different processor core running on a different socket. The A64 3000 on the Socket 754 (what you have) runs at 2ghz while the A64 3000 for Socket 939 (what I have) runs at 1.8ghz. Mine is a newer chip that's smaller and has less heat output as well as supporting dual channel memory but at best that only adds about 5% performance boost. 
<br />

<br />
I really would disable CnQ as it probably doesn't reduce your computer's noise output or temperature by much. I would agree that it is not CnQ's fault but at this point, it's easier (and faster) for you to just switch CnQ off than wait for SoE to fix their timer implementation in EQ. 
<br />

<br />
Since it's a new system check out <a href="http://www.tweakxp.com" target="_blank">http://www.tweakxp.com</a> and <a href="http://www.blackviper.com/WinXP/winxp.htm" target="_blank">http://www.blackviper.com/WinXP/winxp.htm</a> for some tips and tricks to configuring WinXP to run faster as well as freeing up some of the RAM that background programs eat up that you don't need.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
